# Read project context before big work

## When this applies

If the user asks for a **substantial** change—**new feature**, **multi-file refactor**, **API or payload change**, **new template**, **render pipeline change**, **automation integration**, or any implementation where getting **endpoints, paths, or data shapes** wrong would waste time—treat **`context/`** as the **source of truth** for this repo.

**Skip** a full context pass for **trivial** edits (single typo, rename in one file, obvious one-liner) when the risk of contract mismatch is negligible.

## What to do first

1. **Do not** rely only on memory or prior chat turns for contracts, routes, or `templateId` / `data` shapes—those drift from reality (**hallucination risk**).
2. If the relevant facts are **not already** verified in your current context (you have not just read the files), **read the appropriate `context/*.md` files** (use the Read tool) **before** deep planning or writing code.
3. Start from **`context/README.md`** to pick files; use **`context/overview.md`** when the scope is unclear. Use **`context/lesson-learned.md`** when touching integrations, n8n, or known pitfalls.
4. After grounding on docs, **read or search actual code** when the change must match implementation details the docs might not cover (then update docs per the context-sync rule if behavior changes).

## Order of operations

**Ground → plan → execute** (or **ground → execute** for straightforward tasks). Do not lock in a plan based on assumed APIs or folder layout without checking **`context/`** when this rule applies.

## Mapping (quick reference)

| Topic | Read first |
|-------|------------|
| HTTP API, render, webhooks | `context/api-server.md` |
| Compositions, Remotion root | `context/remotion.md` |
| Slides, `templateId`, `data` | `context/templates.md` |
| Branding, effects | `context/effects.md` |
| n8n / external callers | `context/integration-n8n.md` |
| Scripts, tests, env | `context/development.md` |
| Gotchas, past mistakes | `context/lesson-learned.md` |

The table in **`.cursor/rules/context-sync.mdc`** matches maintenance duties; this rule matches **reading** before **doing**.
